    "lastUpdated": "2023-10-10",
    "sourceFile": "Brucella sp., Arthritis.pdf"
  },
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Clinical Setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Subacute or chronic presentation, often preceded by a flu-like illness. Most cases in the U.S. are imported.",
        "History of animal exposure (e.g., veterinarian, farmer, butcher or others with contact to goats, cattle, pigs) or exposure to unpasteurized milk or milk products.",
        "Sacroiliac joint involved in ~60% of cases, spondylodiscitis in ~40% (Intern Med 50:421, 2011).",
        "See Brucella sp. for full disease spectrum"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Diagnosis"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Joint fluid findings often non-specific and synovial fluid cultures sterile;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "diagnosticTest",
      "diagnosticTestData": {
        "name": "Culture",
        "notes": "Slow growing coccobacilli. Can culture from blood, bone marrow, or other body fluids. Sensitivity of culture varies with severity of illness and lab methods employed (15-70%). Inform lab personnel of possible brucella so as to protect technologists from exposure"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "diagnosticTest",
      "diagnosticTestData": {
        "name": "Serology",
        "notes": "Can detect elevated or rising titers of serum antibodies using a variety of techniques, e.g., serum agglutination, ELISA. Be sure to screen with serial dilutions of serum as prozone phenomena can occur."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "diagnosticTest",
      "diagnosticTestData": {
        "name": "Molecular tests (PCR)",
        "notes": "are emerging; Sensitive and can detect organism within 10 days of onset"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Etiologies"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Brucella abortus (cattle)",
        "Brucella melitensis (goats)",
        "Brucella suis (pigs)",
        "Brucella canis (dogs)"
      ]
    },
    {
